    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I realize this might be out of scope for this issue, but since `NetworkConfigurations` now live on the `NetworkController` rather than keeping a record of the full previous provider config, should we just keep `previousProvider` state value of either the provider `type` (in the case of an infura network) or the [networkConfigurationId](https://github.com/MetaMask/core/pull/1064/files#diff-ea0aa37793484e278bd59970b7a6ce8380b75b723b34612081d402fb66261cfdR462) (in the case of a custom network) and then use either [setProviderType](https://github.com/MetaMask/core/blob/ade7255cfdcf6104cf1071bf8a4d227e7fa3d7d0/packages/network-controller/src/NetworkController.ts#L441) or [setActiveNetwork](https://github.com/MetaMask/core/pull/1064/files#diff-ea0aa37793484e278bd59970b7a6ce8380b75b723b34612081d402fb66261cfdR464) to roll it back? cc @Gudahtt @mcmire ",
